    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="361" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Durham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-01-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 17,
                            1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Foster states that the present condition of the negotiations does not
                        justify the use of force, instructs Mr. Durham to lay the President’s
                        instruction, telegraphed to him on this day, before the Haitian Government,
                        and to inform the Department by telegram if the latter makes no offer of
                        indemnity.</p>
            </div>
